 Dhaka, Feb 2 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh open their short tour of New Zealand with a Twenty20 match at Seddon Park, Hamilton on Wednesday. The Tigers, who flew to New Zealand on Jan 29, a day after losing the Test series against India, will be hoping for change in fortune against the Black Caps during the tour involving a one-off Test and three ODIs. However, Bangladesh will be without pace spearhead Mashrafe Bin Mortaza, who failed to recover from a fever, which initially delayed his departure. The paceman, out of action since July, was hoping only to play in the one-dayers and Twenty20 match before returning home. The Bangladesh Cricket Board has already indicated that there no plans to send a replacement for Mashrafe, who underwent knee surgery after the tour of West Indies last year. In his absence Shakib Al Hasan has been leading the side. The T20 starts at noon Bangladesh time on Wednesday. The three one-dayers are on Feb 5, 8 and 11. The one-off Test begins in Hamilton on Fe
